<br>
He pondered and pondered some more until finally he resolved the conflict that ate at him. Reaching a hand into the darkness he pulled on something and immediatley a bell rang. He placed his hand back in its former position and waited patiently until one of his servants opened the door and a flush of brightness poured in from the hall. Poseidon told the man to call for four distinct immortals to come and meet him down in Aigai.<br>
<br>
The man left immediately closing the door shut behing him after being given the orders. He yoked up a pair of immortal horses to a small chariot and set out to send this message to the immortal he was told to give it to. The message was: <br>
<br>
               Greetings,<br>
                          I Poseidon call you to an important meeting at my palace. We shall be discussing the things that are currently happening among the immortals and some of my plans as to how we shall go about putting them into action.<br>
<br>
The messages were to go to Apollo, Iris, Demeter and Artemis. As they were sent out the god waited patiently for their arrival. The candle light jumped and disappeared as Poseidon blew at it. Darkness took over. <p>Poseidon~Lord of the Deep Blue Sea~Patron Of Horses And Sailors~</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ugoddessartemis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Goddess Artemis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 338<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(4/17/02 2:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=247.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/mogoddessartemis/images/triplemoon.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Call for action!!!!!!!!!</span><hr size=1> ~Artemis was siting by a waterfall, a stag by her feet, around her were the animals of the forest. The birds in the tree's sang there beautiful songs as the rabbits hopped aroung playing, a smile sat on her lips. Around her, her nymphs danced and frolicked. She looked up as she heard the distinct sound of a chariot and horses, and smiled as Poseidon's servent approached her. He stepped from him chariot and bowed to her.~<br>
" Oh divine one, Goddess of the Wild, I bring forth to you a scroll from your uncle Poseidon."<br>
~He spoke as he handed her the scroll. She took it with her hand and nodded to him.~<br>
"Thank you servant of Poseidon, you may go."<br>
~Her nymphs giggled at the man and ran to him, placing a ring of wildflowers upon his head, then ran off, to collect more. Artemis herself laughed, as did the servant, he bowed respectfully to the Goddess and was off.~<br>
~Artemis rolled open the scroll and read the contents. What her uncle was talking about, she didnt know...what was going on with the Immortals? She hadnt heard of anything, and she was the one who spent alot of time with them, well, more then any of the others these days anyway. Artemis was always curious, but not more then cautious. She knew her uncle held ill will towards her, and she didnt even know why. She never even cared for that matter. He considered her a brat, she onsidreed him a pompus arrogent fool, full of himself. So she guessed they were even. She rolled up the scroll. It was about the immortals, and for that, she would show civility towards her uncle, no matter what the childish way he might treat her, atleast, she and everyone else knew better. She would go o his palace. But not right away, she would not waste the beautiful day that Demeter bestowed upon them, with her sour uncle.~ <p>~ The Silver Goddess~<br>
