<br>
&quot;And to what do I owe this pleasure?&quot; Apollo smiled walking from the doorway, further into his palace. The servant stood there bewildered as to what to do.<br>
<br>
&quot;Well are you going to just stand there? Or are you going to come in?&quot; Apollo laughed as he poured himself a cup of nectar.<br>
<br>
&quot;I come to you with news from the sea. Your Uncle, The Trident-Bearing Poseidon, Lord of the Earth and of the Sea implores you to come to his palace. He wishes to speak of things concerning the current unrest on Olympus. It would greatly pleasure him if you were to attend.&quot; he handed Apollo the written note, which Apollo snatched up and read quietly to himself.<br>
<br>
&quot;Very well, you may go. But before you do, bring this to him.&quot; Apollo scribbled down on a piece of the finest paper...<br>
<br>
&quot;Dearest Uncle, I would be delighted to stop by at your palacial estate to discuss issues at hand. It has been far too long since our last get together. Do tell me if I should bring anything...<br>
Your beloved nephew, Apollo&quot;<br>
